Description:
A Associação Para Saúde e Desenvolvimento Rural  (ASEDER) é uma organização moçambicana sem fins lucrativos cujos objectivos são:

a)	Promover a educação, a cidadania e a saúde social, incluindo prevenção de HIV-SIDA e consumo de drogas;
b)	Auscultar os problemas sociais da comunidade relacionados com saneamento, agricultura, energias renováveis e acesso a água, buscando soluções locais que se adequem a realidade da mesma;
c)	Promover o respeito aos direitos humanos e igualdade de gênero tomando como base as regulamentações nacionais e internacionais vigentes;
d)	Preservar, defender e conservar o meio ambiente e promover o desenvolvimento sustentável;
e)	Promover iniciativas inovadoras de solidariedade e cooperação para o desenvolvimento rural;
f)	Promover o intercâmbio socioeconômico e cultural local, nacional, regional e global

We seek a more empathetic, democratic, and just world;

A world in which peace and security prevail, human dignity, freedom of expression, kindness, and moderation are celebrated, and extremism and hatred are rejected;

A world where people recognize our shared humanity, are compassionate towards the most vulnerable, and embrace critical thinking and listening skills as a pathway to stronger and more democratic societies.

OUR NETWORK’S GOALS AND OBJECTIVES

CONNECTING: bridging geographic barriers by connecting professionals, entrepreneurs and innovators, who wish to participate in the social and economic development of a new Sudan;

COLLABORATING: facilitating opportunities for individuals and organisations to form successful synergies that contribute to re-energising Sudan’s economy and re-building the country’s social fabric through the implementation of developmental programmes in all facets of society, culture and the economy;

LEADING POSITIVE CHANGE: facilitate opportunities for leaders to emerge through learning and development programmes, who can act as a force for positive change and drive pragmatic developmental programmes;  

DIALOGUE & KNOWLEDGE SHARING: facilitate discussions and knowledge sharing from field experts, who will be key drivers of change;

SETTING STANDARDS: capturing expert and professional opinion and lobby the Sudanese government and international bodies to facilitate the implementation of policy changes and ensure continual social and economic development, better services, robust governance and anti-corruption policies;

REPATRIATION: facilitate opportunities for Sudanese expatriates within Sudan;

EVENTS: host events that focus on creating professional networking opportunities to facilitate business and philanthropic activities. These will include:  
- Networking 
- Conferences
- Learning & development 
- Trade fairs
- Talks, seminars, lectures, webinars

WHAT OUR NETWORK COLOURS REPRESENT
BLUE: Sudan’s plentiful water resources 
YELLOW: Sudan’s rich mineral resources and sun-drenched lands
GREEN: Sudan’s vast and abundant agricultural resources

Da quasi 20 anni l'associazione si impegna per la riduzione dell'inquinamento atmosferico nella città di Milano. 

L'associazione conduce una campagna di azione, per spronare l’amministrazione a mettere in atto e perseguire una vera politica ambientale, e di cultura, per toccare quei luoghi che possano dare un contributo al miglioramento del traffico e dell’inquinamento attraverso iniziative e progetti (scuole, istituzioni comunali, aziende e attività commerciali).

Nel corso degli anni l’associazione ha sostenuto moltissime iniziative:
-   per migliorare le condizioni ambientali della città;
-   per sensibilizzare l’opinione pubblica;
-   per spronare le istituzioni a rendere la città sempre più ivibile, “respirabile” e a misura di persona.

L’associazione si muove su piani differenti:
-  quello legale, con ricorsi al TAR per annullare delibere incoerenti con le politiche antinquinamento;
-   educativo con progetti di educazione ambientale nelle scuole, come il progetto Siamo Nati per camminare;
-   della sensibilizzazione dell’opinione pubblica tramite articoli, interventi, flash mob, e partecipazione attiva a tutti momenti di vita pubblica dove è possibile fare sentire la propria voce;
-  della partecipazione attiva, come il progetto Negozi Amici dell'Aria e TrentaMI.

- Ambrogino d'Oro nel 2013 
- Premio alla Virtù Civica - Panettone d'Oro nel 2013

Stichting Somerset Capital Partners Foundation staat voor het bevorderen van het welzijn van kwetsbaren en het stimuleren van ontwikkeling van talent, financieel of anderszins. De werkzaamheden van de Stichting richten zich momenteel op het ondersteunen van personen, projecten en algemeen nut beogende instellingen op het gebied van: 

welzijn; 
armoedebestrijding; 
(medisch) onderzoek; 
onderwijs; 
talentontwikkeling; 
ondersteuning van (ontwikkeling van) (top)sporters.

The Bradley Impact Fund is a robust, national community of informed donors and partners who support and fund organizations that restore, strengthen, and protect America’s founding principles and institutions. Our mission is to serve as philanthropic advisors who educate, empower, and inspire donors to advance our common principles through high-impact giving and the protection of donor intent.

Bradley Impact Fund Guiding Principles:
- Fidelity to the Constitution, with its principles of limited government, federalism, separation of powers, and individual liberties;
- Commitment to free markets that allow for private enterprise, entrepreneurship, and voluntary exchange within the rule of law;
- Commitment to the fundamental institutions of civil society that cultivate individuals capable of self-governance;
- Dedication to the formation of informed and capable citizens, and
- Protection of donor intent.

We are aligned with and inspired by The Lynde and Harry Bradley Foundation’s mission to restore, strengthen, and protect the principles and institutions of American exceptionalism. The Foundation’s 30 years of philanthropic expertise and vetted portfolio of nonprofit organizations are resources available to our dynamic community.

We invite you to join us. Receive exceptional donor service and multiply your philanthropic influence in our shared effort to preserve and protect conservative American values. To learn more, visit bradleyimpactfund.org, or call us at (414) 291-2500.

OLYMPE est un collectif mixte indépendant formé par des étudiant(e)s de l'emlyon business school qui a pour but de promouvoir l'égalité homme-femme.

OLYMPE fait référence à Olympe de Gouges, considérée comme une des pionnières du féminisme français, et qui a notamment rédigé la « Déclaration des droits de la femme et de la citoyenne » en 1791.
Olympe est aussi l’acronyme d’ « Organisation de Lutte contre la MisogYnie et de Promotion de
l’Egalité Femmes-Hommes».

Nos missions principales sont : 
- Sensibiliser les étudiants aux problématiques du sexisme dans la vie personnelle et professionnelle 
- Promouvoir l’égalité femmes-hommes ;
- Favoriser l’empowerment des femmes ;
- Lutter contre toutes les formes de sexisme dans la vie étudiante, professionnelle et personnelle ;
- (Re)penser les genres et lutter contre les stéréotypes ;
- Engager la réflexion sur les codes sociaux et culturels qui entretiennent le patriarcat et le sexisme au sein de notre société et dans nos entreprises ;
- Apporter des informations aux étudiants au sujet de la nécessité d'une égalité femmes-hommes dans la vie personnelle et professionnelle
- Se tenir disponible et à l’écoute des étudiants et étudiantes.

The Schuler Education Foundation seeks to positively impact individuals and communities by investing in high-achieving underrepresented students and top-tier liberal arts colleges.

Our mission is based on the following beliefs: 
- We believe in the value of a liberal arts education and are committed to preserving this uniquely American tradition;
- We believe that high-achieving, hard-working students in America deserve an opportunity to gain access to top-tier liberal arts colleges and to be supported before, during, and after their college education;
- We recognize that many deserving students entering high school in disadvantaged school districts and under-resourced families lack the tools and guidance necessary to gain admittance to and succeed at top-tier liberal arts colleges;

Therefore, we believe that investing our philanthropic support in high-achieving underrepresented—often first-generation, low-income—students and top-tier American liberal arts colleges will help secure the success of individuals and communities. 

The Schuler Education Foundation currently supports the Schuler Scholar Program and the Schuler Initiative. 

The Foundation does not accept unsolicited grant applications or letters of inquiry, and does not solicit or accept donations.

A Associação São Joaquim de Apoio à Maturidade é uma organização sem fins lucrativos que atua desde 2006 como Centro de Convivência para pessoas idosas em Carapicuíba-SP. Fundamentada na antroposofia e inspirada na salutogênese (forças que geram saúde). Sua metodologia visa o  desenvolvimento integral do Ser humano (cabeça, coração e mãos). 

A Associação São Joaquim contribui com o envelhecimento ativo e saudável, atua pela garantia de direitos da pessoa idosa, seu empoderamento, protagonismo e participação nas políticas públicas, além de apoiar a causa e as ações voltadas à população 60+. 

Os Percursos de Convivência em grupo incluem atividades físicas, manuais, psicossociais, artísticas, cognitivas e de autoconhecimento para 400 pessoas idosas.

Para mais informações acesse: www.saojoaquim.org.br

Visão
Amadurecer é reconhecer a vida.

Missão
Valorizar, por meio da convivência criativa, a história e o desenvolvimento de cada ser humano.

Valores
- Cuidado;
- Respeito;
- Amorosidade;
- Transparência;
- Alegria;
- Criatividade;
- Espiritualidade;

Donate and support the Hobsons Bay Community Fund (HBCF) vision of a harmonious community working to build trust and encourage economic, racial, and social fairness; cultural richness; and environmental sustainability.

To help realise its vision, the HBCF will aim to:

Create a lasting community asset, ensuring Hobsons Bay residents can access in perpetuity, a steadily growing corpus (fund) for community development;
Highlight the great value of charitable giving, and enabling donors to support, and see the fruits of investing in their community during their lifetime;
Encourage interaction and partnerships between a range of people (donors, governments, businesses, community groups, other charitable organisations) to fortify the local community and find solutions to challenges;
Act as a trustworthy partner and leader in shaping collaborative and effective responses to local issues and opportunities.

If you live or work in Hobsons Bay we welcome you to join us to support the community through donating to the Fund which in 2021 stands at $1 million, or participate in our annual Golf Day at Kooringal Golf Club or our annual Business Lunch. Proceeds are returned to the Hobsons Bay community through our annual grants.

The San Luis Obispo County Community Foundation is a public trust established to assist donors in building an enduring source of charitable funds to meet the changing needs and interests of the community.

CORE VALUES
The San Luis Obispo County Community Foundation is committed to achieving impact in areas of relevance to the community. As we go about this work, we want to be known for:

Providing excellent service to donors, grantees, and the community;
Exercising personal and organizational integrity in all our interactions;
Treating everyone with dignity and respect;
Promoting and facilitating collaboration in all our work;
Making a positive difference in the lives of all residents of San Luis Obispo County; and
Maintaining the Foundation as a permanent and enduring community resource.

Animal Foundation Platform reduces the suffering of stray animals abroad by:
 •Stimulating the cooperation between organizations which are involved with stray animals (the effect of the total is bigger than the sum of the individual organizations);
 •Offering practical help to all participating organizations by giving information, exchanging knowledge, skills, materials and financial means;
 •Giving publicity to our work through local, national and international PR campaigns;
 •Joining our forces so we, as an umbrella organization, can achieve more than each individual organization separately.
 
Focus 
The Focus of AFP is on TNR and education. Scientific studies  show that TNR is feasible at all times and helps reduce stray populations. TNR is short for Trap Neuter  and Return which means free roaming dogs and dogs who do have owners are collected, sterilised, vaccinated labelled and taken back to where they had come from.

We're the go-to people for volunteering in the London Borough of Sutton.

Volunteer Centre Sutton has over 50 years' expertise in helping local people find positive volunteering opportunities and supporting organisations attract and develop great volunteer teams.

But we’ve also innovated, identifying and responding to unmet need in Sutton by:
- introducing alternative, more flexible ways for people to volunteer;
- increasing our delivery of quality support and training for organisations;
- developing award-winning volunteering projects like MAPS (Mentoring Advocacy Peer Support), Sutton Befrienders and Citizens Commissioning.

Pangea Giving is a giving circle whose purpose is to give its members and supporters direct, thoughtful and effective ways to support grassroots organizations in developing countries to improve the quality of life in their community.

• We make grants in places where there are high levels of poverty and vulnerability to human rights abuses;
• We believe that lasting change is built from the ground up;
• Our grants support the self-defined needs of local communities, and build the capacity of community organizations and leadership to meet those needs.

For more information on our work and how you can become involved, check out our website.

“United for a better world to make a positive difference”. The Best of the World Network is a non-profit organization focusing on a global and regional cooperation and valuable connections based on human values and philanthropic ideals. The initial idea started with The Best of Marbella and The Best of Vienna. Already in 2009, WE Magazine for Women in USA acknowledged our efforts as “one of 101 bloggers to watch in 2009”. Since then, The Best of Marbella and Vienna transformed to a global promotional platform and peace project with the best references and testimonials and approximately 200 valuable cooperation partners.

Our objectives are:
•	To share positive and useful information; encourage and promote the cross-cultural understanding, integration and dialogue among all cultures and nations;
•	To support the promotion of cultural and touristic highlights of every country in the world including investment opportunities
•	Feature the most inspirational projects and visionary personalities from every countries (including leaders, charities, NGO´s, peace building projects and personalities, inter-cultural and environmental projects);
•	To foster peace and friendship regardless of cultural, economical, religious or social backgrounds; promoting social corporate responsibility and environmental awareness;
•	To empower and inspire people to do their BEST and share the best practice examples and success stories from all countries in the world and many walks of life;
•	Connect people and businesses with synergies and enable everyone to express their greatest potentials and while doing so achieve recognition, prosperity, success, abundance and quality of life;
•	Create networking opportunities and long-term cooperation including our existing network of approx 200 cooperation partners;
More information: www.thebestoftheworld.info

Desde 1982, quando foi fundado, o LAR DA REDENÇÃO objetiva dar amor, atenção e cuidados às crianças especiais, portadoras de deficiências físicas, mentais, severas e irreversíveis, oriundas de famílias sem recursos.

Em 1986, o LAR DA REDENÇÃO adquiriu e iniciou a construção da sua sede própria no bairro da Mooca. Até então, funcionou no bairro de Jardim América, em local emprestado.

Um grupo de abnegados cidadãos, conscientes da importância da solidariedade e da dignidade humana vem permitindo a continuidade dos trabalhos.

Sua ajuda é especial, porque suas doações mensais, seu trabalho voluntário, tem mantido as atividades do dia a dia e permitido promover diversos eventos, tais como bazares, rifas, festas típicas, gerando os recursos necessários.

Pontos fortes do LAR DA REDENÇÃO:
Estrutura familiar;
Idealismo e empenho;
Ausência da ânsia de poder;
Diretoria aberta a novas propostas;
Integração entre profissionais e voluntários;
Convivência mútua de diferentes níveis sociais.

Missão
Oferecer moradia e tratamento adequado a crianças especiais portadoras de deficiência física mental e múltipla, em condição de abandono e maus tratos, desenvolvendo ao máximo suas potencialidades enquanto houver prognostico reabilitacional. Promover a intervenção precoce para quando possível, facilitar sua autonomia e inclusão social.

Visão
Ser uma instituição voltada ao aprimoramento constante da qualidade técnica, humana e organizacional, visando o bem estar do portador de necessidades especiais e promovendo o seu desenvolvimento como cidadão.

Valores
Respeito às necessidades individuais do portador de necessidades especiais;
Acreditar que o portador de necessidades especiais pode ser uma oportunidade de aprendizado para o nosso crescimento como seres humanos;
Acreditar que todo ser humano é capaz independente de suas limitações;
Integração entre profissionais e voluntários.

GOPIO FRANCE METROPOLE a pour objectifs :

> promouvoir les intérêts et les aspirations de la communauté indienne ;
> promouvoir le patrimoine culturel indien et créer une relation durable ;
> mobiliser des ressources financières, intellectuelles et professionnelles des Indiens pour le développement mutuel dans son pays d'adoption ;
> encourager l'interaction entre les communautés pour délibérer et décider sur des sujets et des problèmes communs ;
> favoriser l'interaction entre les PIO (Personnes d"Origine Indienne) et d'autres communautés dans le but de promouvoir la paix, le progrès et l'harmonie ;
> aider à la mise en œuvre en tant que diaspora et créer des synergies avec la forte croissance économique de l'Inde ;
> assurer un rôle de facilitateur entre la diaspora indienne vivant en France et avec l'Inde pour des avantages socio-économiques.

Founded in 2014, the European Foundation for Cambodian Children (EFCC) is an NGO operating in Phnom Penh. Its mission is to provide access to education for the most vulnerable children, whose parents can not afford to send them to school. EFCC supports children until they become autonomous and enter the labour market. After years of action, EFCC welcomes more than 60 children, aged 3 to 18 every day. EFCC works with the local community, employing only Cambodians and regularly helping children's families (by providing them with rice, bread, medical products, clothes, etc.). 

We operate with an average of 6 to 8 volunteers. They offer their skills and experience to the benefit of the development of the NGO in the following areas: 

• Marketing and Communication (project management, growth hacking, social networks, WordPress, graphic design, etc.); 
• Finding new partnerships and sponsorships; 
• Management and Accounting; 
• Audiovisual (photography and video production). 

In addition, our volunteers support children in certain aspects of daily life (supervision of meals, manual and sports activities). 

If you want to join us as a volunteer, you can apply directly by sending us your resume and cover letter at info@efcc.ngo

If you want to become our partner or sponsor children, visit our website https://efcc.ngo/en/home/ and contact us at info@efcc.ngo

ASRADD est une organisation de la société civile à but non lucratif, apolitique et non confessionnelle. Elle conduit des actions de développement durable et vise à améliorer l’accès aux services sociaux de base, améliorer le cadre de vie et a protéger l’environnement pour le bien-être des populations africaines en général et sahélienne en particulier afin d’atteindre les objectifs de développement durable.
Elle travaille en appui, en collaboration et en partenariat avec les Associations nationales et/ou internationales des secteurs publics et privés qui poursuivent les objectifs similaires. 
Afin de mieux répondre aux besoins des populations, ASRADD a développé un réseau international qui vise les mêmes objectifs à savoir :
⮚	Améliorer la santé de la population ;
⮚	Lutter contre la malnutrition et l’insécurité alimentaire ;
⮚	Améliorer l’éducation de base ;
⮚	Améliorer l’accès à l’eau potable, à l’hygiène et à l’assainissement ;
⮚	Assister les populations en situation d’urgence ;
⮚	Appuyer les communautés de base par des activités génératrices de revenu ;
⮚	Lutter contre la détérioration des conditions écologiques et des écosystèmes ;
⮚	Promouvoir et vulgariser la utilisation des énergies renouvelables ;

CIA DOS CLOWNATICOS - Associação companhia dos ClownAticos.

Somos uma associação sem fins lucrativos que atua e desenvolve suas ações em:
- Casas de apoio às crianças e aos adolescentes com câncer;
- Casas de assistência à criança e ao adolescente cardíaco e transplantados do coração;
- Escolas públicas para jovens;
- Institutos e Outras Organizações parceiras;
- Comunidades carentes, em geral.

Nossas atividades são direcionadas para dois pilares principais: arte e desenvolvimento humano. Buscamos promover o crescimento, aprendizado e aprimoramento artístico de nossos voluntários, assim como oferecer apoio solidário e humanitário aos beneficiários por nossas ações.

Mwabonwa means welcome, and Kondanani means “Love One Another”.  Kondanani Zambia Inc. is a registered charity in Australia that focuses on supporting Children who are Disabled, Orphan and Vulnerable  in Zambia. Its founders,  Jenny and John Preston, have been involved in Zambia since 1992.

Our Mission is 

To ensure that every child, especially those disadvantaged in any way, can actualize their full human potential, realise their rights and experience what it means to be a human being fully alive.

Since 1996 the Association and its partners have shared in the provision of financial and practical  support for the following projects.

- Establishing the Bissell Farm Community School;
- Developing the Kalalaska Village Community School;
- Support of the Vision of Hope Community School;
- Support of the Garden Compound Community School;
- Skills training for young people at Chodort Training Centre, Choma;
- Provision of Solar Power to Community Schools;
- Provision of student buraries;
- Provision of clothing, school books, library books, carpentry tools, sewing machines, dressmaking materials and computers;
- Provision of food for schools’ feeding programs;
- Disability Projects including:-
- Children with Hearing Impaired by providing new and second hand hearing aids,  audiometers and hearing aid testing equipment to the Zambian National Association of the Hearing Impaired;
- Sight Impaired children and adults by providing second hand specitals to the Zambia Open Community Schools and the Lusaka Eye Hospital

The Japanese American Women Alumnae of UC Berkeley (JAWAUCB) is an official chapter of the California Alumni Association. The purposes of JAWAUCB are to:

1.  honor the recipients of the undergraduate and graduate scholarship and fellowship awards from the JAWAUCB Endowment Fund established by agreement with the Regents of the University of California;

2.  promote donations, gifts, and bequests for the continued growth of the JAWAUCB Endowment Fund in honor and recognition of the achievements of its founders;

3.  support research, educational, and leadership development efforts focused on or related to Japanese American, Asian, Asian American and Pacific Islander (AAPI) women;

4.  foster a network of UC Berkeley students, staff, faculty, alumni, and members of the larger community in support of and service to our alma mater.

Le Mouvement Pact créé en 1942 pour lutter contre les taudis et le mal logement. est constitué de 145 associations réparties sur tout le territoire et constitue un réseau de professionnels dans le domaine de l’habitat privé social. L’objectif commun des Pact est de contribuer, en améliorant la qualité de leur habitat, à l’épanouissement des personnes.

Le PACT Yvelines, c’est aujourd’hui :
Une équipe pluridisciplinaire locale de 30 collaborateurs qui mobilisent les compétences acquises par l’ensemble du réseau PACT.
Une compétence reconnue par l’Etat, la Région, le Département, les collectivités locales.
Le PACT est dans les Yvelines, l’interlocuteur privilégié de tous les organismes publics et privés apportant leurs concours à l’amélioration de l’habitat.
Des services « sur mesure » apportés aux communautés et aux communes, définis par les élus, dans le cadre de conventions qui précisent ses missions et ses moyens pour atteindre leurs objectifs : améliorer et adapter l’habitat existant, remettre en service des logements vacants, conduire une politique locale de l’habitat et accompagner des ménages dans leur projet d’habitat.

Améliorer l'habitat des yvelinois, en priorité celui des plus démunis c'est :
- Adapter le logement au handicap ou à la dépendance ;
- Lutter contre l'habitat indigne et la précarité énergétique ;
- Aider les copropriétés fragiles ;
- Accompagner les parcours résidentiels ;
- Développer l'offre de logement à loyer maitrisé

Our mission is to positively impact the Athens community by providing young professionals opportunities for networking, community involvement and leadership advancement.

“We Believe . . .
That faith in God gives meaning and purpose to human life;
That the brotherhood of man transcends the sovereignty of nations;
That economic justice can best be won by free men through free enterprise;
That government should be of laws rather than of men;
That earth’s great treasure lies in human personality;
And that service to humanity is the best work of life!”

The Giuliana and Giorgio Stefanini Foundation is a non-profit, public interest Organization. It is fully independent and has no political or religious constraints.

The Foundation aims at promoting and providing financial support to targeted projects in the field of:
- cancer research, clinical studies and treatment of cancer;
- visual arts (conservation and restoration);
- classical music.


Die Giuliana und Giorgio Stefanini Stiftung ist eine anerkannte gemeinnützige, Nonprofit-Organisation. Sie ist politisch und religiös unabhängig.

Die Stiftung bezweckt die Förderung und Unterstützung gezielter Projekte in den folgenden Bereichen:
- Krebsforschung, klinische Studien und Behandlung von Krebs;
- Bildende Kunst;
- Klassische Musik.

Cette mission humanitaire, organisée par des élèves d'AgroParisTech agit dans la région reculée de Ganesh Himal au Népal. 

Elle a pour  objectifs:
- D'ameliorer l'ouverture touristique de la région Ganesh Himal par l'apprentissage de l'anglais;
- Apporter un soutien médical;
- Apporter du matériel scolaire, sportif, éducatif et médical;
- Etablir et sensibiliser aux problématiques environementales et sanitaires.

OUR MISSION
1.  Raising awareness for Veterans seeking a potential alternative to prosthetics through arm/hand transplants;
2.  Connecting our Veterans with the applicable transplant programs that can best serve them;
3.  Raising funds through donations and grants, covering the gap for associated procedures and long-term care; and to
4.  Return the Salute

For more information, please contact us at Info@ReturnTheSalute.org

Le Programme de consolidation de l’état et du monde associatif
Le Pro-CEMA vise à mieux impliquer la société civile dans l’accompagnement de l’action gouvernementale, la gestion des affaires publiques/redevabilité et à assurer une meilleure coordination État-Monde Associatif. Il attache une attention particulière à la dimension genre et vise notamment à encourager les candidatures féminines et à accroître la présence des femmes aux postes électifs. Il permet enfin au milieu culturel de mieux participer au débat citoyen. Il s’étend sur l’ensemble du territoire pour une durée d’intervention de quarante (40) mois dont 3 mois de clôture.
Quatre résultats essentiels sont attendus à l’issue du programme :
R1 : Les faitières des OSC, professionnelles et représentatives, sont capables de renforcer les capacités de leurs membres, en particulier des femmes et de jeunes filles, à jouer pleinement leur rôle d’acteur de développement et de contrôle de l’action gouvernementale ;
R2 : L’État assure la promotion, la supervision et le dialogue avec le monde associatif ;
R3 : La participation des femmes et des jeunes filles à la vie publique et politique ainsi qu’à la gestion des affaires locales est accrue ;
R4 : Le monde culturel s’intègre dans des actions de dialogue de la société civile et dispose de meilleures conditions afin de participer au débat citoyen

The Paula Ford-Martin Memorial Fund was established in 2020 to honor the life of Paula Ford-Martin, a devoted mother of LGBTQ+ children and a fierce advocate for social justice. Her namesake memorial fund provides scholarship monies for LGBTQ+ students and their allies who demonstrate: (1) outstanding commitment to advocacy for the LGBTQ+ community, and (2) firm plans to pursue college, university, vocational training, or any post-secondary educational endeavor.

The specific objectives of this organization are:
     a. to provide scholarship funds for LGBTQ+ youth and their allies;
     b. to promote visibility and advocacy for the LGBTQ+ community;
     c. to support initiatives promoting equitable access to housing, health care, legal services, and other necessities for LGBTQ+ youth and families.

***The Paula Ford-Martin Memorial Fund is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization, EIN 85-0999059. All donations are tax-deductible.***

Международная общественная организация "Боевое Братство" привлекает внимание общественности России и других стран к проблемам ветеранов и инвалидов, к вопросам их социализации и реабилитации после возвращения к гражданской жизни.

"Боевое Братство" помогает углубить сотрудничество и развить новые формы творческого взаимодействия людей всех стран, расширения международных контактов, развития культурного обмена между странами.

Наши задачи:
- Развитие и поддержка, укрепление социально-культурных, творческих, спортивных связей между странами и людьми;
- Создание единого творческого пространства «Боевое братство»;
- Привлечение внимания к Маршу и поддержка творческих личностей в создании произведений тематики «Боевое братство». 


International public organization "Battle Brotherhood " draws attention to the problems of different countries and disabled veterans , to the issues of their socialization and rehabilitation after returning to civilian life. 

"Battle Brotherhood " helps deepen cooperation and develop new forms of creative interaction among people of all countries, the expansion of international contacts and the development of cultural exchange between countries. 

Our objectives : 
- Develop and support , strengthening the socio- cultural, artistic , sporting relations between countries and peoples ; 
- Creation of a single creative space «Battle Vrotherhood "; 
- Raising awareness of the International March of Veterans and support creative individuals in the creation of works subject «Battle Brotherhood ."

Maddie’s Mark Foundation was established in early 2012 to honor Madeline Musto. An independent, vibrant 5 year old who was taken away from the world too quickly by an inoperable brain stem tumor (DIPG).  The foundation's mission is to spread Madeline's spirit by providing opportunities, creating environments, and enabling people and families to live a life of 'best days ever'.

The goals of the foundation are a reflection of Madeline’s outlook on life. All support and donations will be going toward these goals:

Maddie’s Mark provides ‘best days ever’ for children suffering from major illness, and provides support for their families;

Maddie’s Mark actively encourages child enrichment, through financial grants to improve public and private entertainment, educational and athletic facilities for children - including schools, parks, playgrounds, and theaters; 

and, Maddie's Mark honors Madeline’s legacy and love of learning through a scholarship program, to provide meaningful and significant financial assistance to remarkable young women.

 We appreciate your generous contributions and support. Thank you for helping Maddie leave her mark!

Санкт-Петербургская благотворительная общественная организация

УКРЕПИТЬ ЖИЗНЬ. ДАТЬ НАДЕЖДУ. ВОЗРОДИТЬ ОБЩЕСТВО

Пристань помогает детям и подросткам группы риска, содействует в становлении их личности, подготавливает их к самостоятельной и успешной жизни в обществе, основываясь на семейных ценностях. 

Пристань работает в областях:
- социальной и бытовой адаптации воспитанников и выпускников детских домов, приютов и др. сиротских учреждений, а также детей и подростков из неблагополучных семей;
- профессиональной ориентации воспитанников и выпускников детских домов;
- материальной и психологической помощи матерям одиночкам.

Пристань содействует:
- в укреплении престижа и роли семьи в обществе;
- деятельности в сфере образования, науки, культуры, искусства, просвещения;
- в духовном развитии личности;
- в укреплении мира, дружбы и согласия в обществе;
- в предотвращении социальных конфликтов.

L’Association TIE est une structure privée de protection des enfants créée le 1er juin 1995 et reconnue officiellement par récépissé N° 96-215/ MDTS / PHUE /HC /DAG du 10 octobre 1996. 
Tié signifie « présence » en langue bôbô. Elle traduire la volonté et l’engagement de ses créateurs de marquer une présence protectrice et éducative auprès des enfants en difficultés notamment ceux en situation de rue.
La mission essentielle de l’Association TIE est de promouvoir et de protéger les droits de l’enfant.
Les objectifs de TIE sont:
•	Favoriser la réinsertion familiale et l’intégration socioéconomique des enfants en situation de rue ;
•	Prévenir la délinquance juvénile ;
•	Lutter contre le trafic, la traite et l’exploitation sexuelle des enfants ;
•	Lutter contre les violences faites aux enfants ;
•	Accompagner les victimes de violences par la prise en charge psychologique, juridique et socioéconomique ;
•	Œuvrer pour l’épanouissement des enfants en difficultés à travers les activités socioculturelles ;
•	 Sensibiliser les populations sur les IST/VIH/SIDA et autres fléaux ;
•	Renforcer la collaboration avec d’autres partenaires poursuivant les mêmes objectifs.

L'association PhysioTraveler a été créée sous l’impulsion de quatre jeunes kinésithérapeutes français en novembre 2017. D'après ses statuts, elle a pour objectifs d’établir une relation privilégiée avec des structures de soin étrangères qui possèdent un service de physiothérapie ainsi que de permettre à des physiothérapeutes diplômés d’y réaliser des missions, répondant aux besoins réels sur place.

Sur place, nous agissons de différentes façons :
- Soutient aux projets de développement du centre ;
- Envoi de kinésithérapeutes en renfort pour des missions bien définies à l'avance ;
- Mise en place de formations et d'échanges de compétences entre les professionnels locaux et étrangers ;
- Si nécessaire, un apport matériel.
